# Code owners — security-sensitive paths require review.
#
# When the agent self-merges a PR, GitHub still allows it without owner
# approval on private repos without branch protection. CODEOWNERS becomes
# binding once you add branch protection (paid plans) or once a paying
# customer/contributor cares.
#
# Until then, this file documents WHICH paths are sensitive even if it
# doesn't yet enforce review. The agent reads CODEOWNERS and treats
# matching paths as "human-only" zones.

# --- Examples to adapt per project -----------------------------------------

# Authentication and tokens
# src/auth/*                     @your-handle
# src/pair/*                     @your-handle

# Billing / payments
# src/billing/*                  @your-handle

# Module loader / plugin system (changes here re-route every module)
# src/core/loader.py             @your-handle

# Logging redaction (single point of credential leakage)
# src/logging/*                  @your-handle

# CI workflows (changes here can disable the safety gates)
# .github/workflows/*            @your-handle

# Secrets and configuration templates
# .env.example                   @your-handle
# docker/Dockerfile.*            @your-handle
